{"id":24231,"title":"Ventilator-associated pneumonia due to carbapenem-resistant Gram-negative bacilli in an intensive care unit without carbapenemase-producing Enterobacteriaceae or epidemic Acinetobacter baumannii.","abstract":"Risk factors for ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP) caused by carbapenem-resistant Gram-negative bacilli (CR-GNB) have rarely been evaluated in intensive care units (ICU) without epidemic carbapenemase-producing Acinetobacter baumannii or Enterobacteriaceae. We addressed this issue in a cohort of 141 patients (previous antimicrobial exposure, n = 131) with a first episode of VAP in a medico-surgical ICU. Twenty-six VAP (18.4%) involved a CR-GNB (Pseudomonas aeruginosa, n = 14, Stenotrophomonas maltophilia, n = 11, and A. baumannii, n = 1), without previous carbapenem exposure in 12 (46.1%) cases. GNB resistant to all ?-lactams except carbapenems were equally isolated in CR-GNB VAP (co-infections, 23%) and other episodes (30%). Previous exposure to aminoglycosides (odds ratio (OR) 1.14 per day, 95% confidence interval (CI) 1.02-1.30, p = 0.02) and the number of antimicrobial classes used before VAP (OR 1.38 per class, 95% CI 1.10-1.73, p = 0.006) were the only independent predictors of CR-GNB. These results suggest that the empirical use of a carbapenem-colistin combination should be evaluated in late-onset VAP following broad-spectrum antimicrobial exposure.","date":"2014-02-17","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24447250","annotations":[{"name":"Pseudomonas aeruginosa","weight":0.901385,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudomonas_aeruginosa"},{"name":"Enterobacteriaceae","weight":0.899002,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enterobacteriaceae"},{"name":"Carbapenem","weight":0.896071,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbapenem"},{"name":"Acinetobacter baumannii","weight":0.878472,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acinetobacter_baumannii"},{"name":"Pneumonia","weight":0.834549,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pneumonia"},{"name":"Aminoglycoside","weight":0.819111,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aminoglycoside"},{"name":"Acinetobacter","weight":0.801553,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acinetobacter"},{"name":"Antimicrobial","weight":0.783697,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial"},{"name":"Stenotrophomonas maltophilia","weight":0.775647,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stenotrophomonas_maltophilia"},{"name":"Pseudomonas","weight":0.734616,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pseudomonas"},{"name":"Intensive care unit","weight":0.722869,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive_care_unit"},{"name":"Stenotrophomonas","weight":0.651122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stenotrophomonas"},{"name":"Bacillus","weight":0.631206,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacillus"},{"name":"Antibiotic resistance","weight":0.542761,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibiotic_resistance"},{"name":"Odds ratio","weight":0.437999,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odds_ratio"},{"name":"Epidemic","weight":0.421978,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemic"},{"name":"Confidence interval","weight":0.348912,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Confidence_interval"},{"name":"Intensive-care medicine","weight":0.278431,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive-care_medicine"},{"name":"Empirical","weight":0.0849722,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empirical"},{"name":"Risk factor","weight":0.0301868,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk_factor"},{"name":"VAP (company)","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VAP_(company)"},{"name":"Hypothermia","weight":0.0217362,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikip